modules.description: This module defines data types and conversion functions for representing WebAssembly modules in various forms—files, raw data, and URLs—within an Extism manifest. It supports serialization to and from JSON using `yojson`, enabling precise handling of Wasm module sources with optional metadata like names, hashes, and request parameters. Use cases include constructing and serializing manifest entries for Wasm modules loaded from disk, embedded data, or remote URLs.

This module enables configuring WebAssembly plugin execution with memory limits, host access controls, and timeouts by constructing and modifying manifest structures that define Wasm module loading parameters. It operates on manifest data types and Wasm modules, providing JSON serialization and memory constraint adjustment capabilities. These features are particularly useful for securely sandboxing plugins with precise resource boundaries in embedded systems or multi-tenant environments.
